parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent pop-up advertisements on the multimedia screen can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Frequent pop-up advertisements on the multimedia screen
requiring drivers to take their eyes off the road to dismiss the ads
disrupting navigation and other essential functions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Blind Spot Monitoring and Collision Warning System Malfunctions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning blind spot monitoring and collision warning systems can cause accidents or near-misses, as drivers may not be aware of vehicles in their blind spots or potential collisions.
symptoms: False or inconsistent warnings
failure to detect vehicles in blind spots
and random beeping or warning lights without apparent reasons.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Lower Bumper Cover Assembly Detachment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the front lower bumper cover assembly can cause accidents or damage to vehicles, as well as harm to passengers and pedestrians.
symptoms: The bumper cover assembly detaches while driving
potentially causing damage or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous explosion of the sunroof or water leakage into the vehicle can cause accidents or distractions while driving.
symptoms: Sudden explosion of the sunroof
water leakage into the vehicle
or droplets of water entering the car near the sunroof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lagging or hesitation of the vehicle can cause accidents or near-misses, particularly in stop-and-go traffic or when merging onto highways.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitation or lagging
sudden surges of power
or bucking when accelerating from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high engine coolant temperature can cause engine damage or failure, potentially leading to accidents or breakdowns.
symptoms: Warning messages indicating high engine coolant temperature
temperature gauge needle jumping to high
or temperature staying at high for extended periods.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Damage and Sunroof Design Flaws
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water damage or design flaws in the sunroof can cause leaks or water entry into the vehicle, potentially leading to electrical or mechanical issues.
symptoms: Water damage or leaks near the sunroof
incorrect sunroof glass angle
or water droplets entering the car near the sunroof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud wind noise can cause distractions or discomfort while driving, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Loud wind noise while driving
particularly at higher speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Lower Bumper Cover Assembly Detachment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the front lower bumper cover assembly can cause damage to the vehicle's structure, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front lower bumper cover assembly detaches while driving
creating holes in the lower front bumper
and visible damage to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Front Lower Bumper Cover Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed availability of parts for the recall repair can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The contact receives notification of the recall
but the parts are not yet available
and the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion through the A pillars can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical systems, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Water enters the vehicle through the A pillars
causing water damage to the interior upholstery and potentially leading to mold growth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation and bucking of the engine can cause a delay in acceleration, leading to potential accidents, especially when merging into traffic or crossing intersections. This issue can also lead to a loss of control, as the vehicle's unpredictable behavior can cause the driver to panic.
symptoms: The engine hesitates or bucks when accelerating
especially from a dead stop; the vehicle surges or lags when pressing the accelerator; the engine struggles to accelerate
feeling like it's "spitting and bucking"; the vehicle has a delayed response to accelerator input
leading to a loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained engine coolant temperature high warning can cause the driver to become distracted, leading to potential accidents. If the issue is not addressed, it can also cause engine damage or overheating.
symptoms: The engine coolant temperature gauge suddenly jumps to maximum; the needle hunts from normal to high; the warning light comes on
even though the dealer cannot find any issues.
